{2\cos(\theta/2)-1-\cos\theta\over2\cos(\theta/2)+1+\cos\theta}={1-\cos(\theta/2)\over1+\cos(\theta/2)}
\cos \theta = 2\cos^2\frac{\theta}{2} - 1
\begin{align}\frac{2\cos\frac{\theta}{2} - 1 - \cos\theta}{2\cos\frac{\theta}{2} + 1 + \cos\theta} &= \frac{2\cos\frac{\theta}{2} - 2\cos^2\frac{\theta}{2}}{2\cos\frac{\theta}{2} + 2\cos^2\frac{\theta}{2}}\\ &= \frac{1 - \cos\frac{\theta}{2}}{1 + \cos\frac{\theta}{2}}\end{align}
\cos(\theta)=\cos^2(\theta)-\sin^2(\theta)
1=\sin^2(\theta)+\cos^2(\theta)
 \frac{2\cos(\theta/2)-2\cos^2(\theta/2)}{2\cos(\theta/2+2\cos^2(\theta/2)}=\frac{2\cos(\theta/2)(1-\cos(\theta/2))}{2\cos(\theta/2)(1+\cos(\theta/2))}=\frac{1-\cos(\theta/2)}{1+\cos(\theta/2)} 
\alpha = \theta/2
 2\cos\alpha - 1 - \cos2\alpha \\ = 2\cos\alpha - (\cos^2\alpha + \sin^2\alpha) - (\cos^2\alpha - \sin^2\alpha) \\ = 2\cos\alpha - 2\cos^2\alpha \\ = 2\cos\alpha(1 - \cos\alpha) 
